<!-- this is the comment line separating the mechanical code from the creative text --><center>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 120%; color: #cc6600;">Catastrophe</span></strong></p>
</center>
<p>You are a poem</p>
<p>a sneaky idea</p>
<p>that crawls through the room</p>
<p>and sleeps past noon</p>
<p>and noisily grooms while we think through</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">Why it's so important</p>
<p>that the sky is blue</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">and the sea full of fish</p>
<p>that skitter and swoon</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">and get caught on the claws</p>
<p>of poems like you</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">so you can leave them</p>
<p>on your favorite one's shoes</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">and she'll hoist you up</p>
<p>with rough hands and a croon</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">and decide, next time</p>
<p>that she'll walk down with you</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">to the edge of the water</p>
<p>on a bright afternoon</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">and teach you to watch</p>
<p>instead of harpoon</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">and as you half-listen</p>
<p>her hands shiver and smooth</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">out the ripples of skin</p>
<p>that collect around you</p>
<p style="padding-left: 60px;">when you sprawl out like this</p>
<p>as you often do</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>because you are a poem</p>
<p>a sneaky idea</p>
<p>that crawls through the room</p>
<p>and sleeps past noon</p>
<p>and kills like you were born to.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
